{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, the double-content examples tend to be enriched with self-explanation prompts and/or additional instructional explanations.",
    "Reflective Prompts.",
    "According to the self-explanation effect, learners benefit more from the examples if they can actively explain the examples to themselves (Wong et al., 2002).",
    "Furthermore, the quality of the self-explanations determines what is learned from the examples (Chi et al., 1989).",
    "However, frequently, learners' selfexplanations are superficial or passive."
  ]
}